## Required CSS on `.stf__item` (src/index.css)

```css
.album-flipbook .stf__item {
  background-color: #fff;
  transform-style: flat !important;
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

- `transform-style: flat !important` — Prevents page content from participating in the parent's 3D stacking in a way that causes compositor glitches during `rotateY` flip.
- `overflow: hidden` — Hard clip boundary. Even if a photo somehow has `overflow: visible`, content cannot escape the page rectangle.
- `background-color: #fff` — Ensures opaque pages; prevents destination page content from showing through transparent areas.

**Do NOT remove or weaken any of these three properties.**

---

## SpreadPage + EditorCanvas mirror layout (f135345 / 3e93e18 line)

**EditorCanvas** — the `div` that wraps `<HTMLFlipBook>` uses `transform: scaleX(-1)` (with opacity transition as needed) so the book matches RTL reading order at the viewport level.

**SpreadPage** — **one** root node: `ref` + `data-density="hard"` + `dir="rtl"` + page chrome (`backgroundColor`, `width`/`height`, `position: relative`, `overflow: hidden`) + **`transform: 'scaleX(-1)'` on that same node**. `PageBackground`, ornaments, and `Absolute` / `Legacy` content are **direct children** — no extra inner wrapper used only to hold the mirror.

The page-flip runtime applies its own `transform` on `.stf__item` during the flip; the product’s validated layout keeps RTL via the **pairing** of editor-level mirror + per-page mirror (same approach as the commits that removed the `isNearby` placeholder regression).

---

## DO NOT (hard rules)

| Action | Why it breaks |
|--------|--------------|
| Call `setCurrentSpread` from `onFlip` | Store / `isCurrent` updates mid-flip → wrong layer or “jumping” content |
| Add `isNearby` (or similar) placeholder branch — empty page vs full content | **Core flash bug:** subtree swap when index changes mid-flip |
| Add `backfaceVisibility: hidden` to SpreadPage root | GPU glitch with `scaleX(-1)` mirror |
| Pass interaction state as props to SpreadPage | Breaks `flipPages` memoization → `updateFromHtml()` |
| Use `style={{}}` on HTMLFlipBook | New object every render → breaks `React.memo` |
| Call `flipNext()`/`flipPrev()` without `deselectAll()` first | `overflow: visible` on selected photo leaks across pages |
| Remove `onChangeState` → `deselectAll` / `read` handlers | Swipe flips skip deselect; store drifts from book |
| Remove `overflow: hidden` from `.stf__item` CSS | Last line of defense against content leaking between pages |
| Remove `transform-style: flat !important` from `.stf__item` | Compositor conflicts during flip |
| Add `AnimatePresence` or exit animations to page content | Ghost elements persist during flip, causing visual artifacts |
